stylometry: The relationship between price and demand that we must consider when setting a price is that, in economics, there is an inverse relationship between price and demand.  That is, as price rises, demand falls.  Similarly, as prices fall, demand increases.  The management decision is to determine an optimal price and the correlating demand in order to maximize profit.  To develop a model, we could use levels of demand as input variables and price as a changing variable, then use solver to maximize profit by changing price.
